0x0000.Name: GPSVersionID
0x0000.Description: Version of the Global Positioning Systems (GPS) IFD, given as 2.0.0.0. This tag is mandatory when the GpsIFD tag is present. When the version is 2.0.0.0, the tag value is 0x02000000.

0x0001.Name: GPSLatitudeRef
0x0001.Description: Indicates whether the latitude is north or south latitude. The ASCII value 'N' indicates north latitude, and 'S' is south latitude.

0x0002.Name: GPSLatitude
0x0002.Description: Indicates the latitude. The latitude is expressed as three RATIONAL values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds, respectively. When degrees, minutes and seconds are expressed, the format is dd/1,mm/1,ss/1. When degrees and minutes are used and, for example, fractions of minutes are given up to two decimal places, the format is dd/1,mmmm/100,0/1.

0x0003.Name: GPSLongitudeRef
0x0003.Description: Indicates whether the longitude is east or west longitude. The ASCII value 'E' indicates east longitude, and 'W' is west longitude.

0x0004.Name: GPSLongitude
0x0004.Description: Indicates the longitude. The longitude is expressed as three RATIONAL values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds, respectively. When degrees, minutes and seconds are expressed, the format is ddd/1,mm/1,ss/1. When degrees and minutes are used and, for example, fractions of minutes are given up to two decimal places, the format is ddd/1,mmmm/100,0/1.

0x0006.Name: GPSAltitude
0x0006.Description: Altitude, in meters, based on the reference altitude specified by GpsAltitudeRef.

0x0007.Name: GPSTimeStamp
0x0007.Description: Time as coordinated universal time (UTC). The value is expressed as three rational numbers that give the hour, minute, and second.

0x0008.Name: GpsSatellites
0x0008.Description: Specifies the GPS satellites used for measurements. This tag can be used to specify the ID number, angle of elevation, azimuth, SNR, and other information about each satellite. The format is not specified. If the GPS receiver is incapable of taking measurements, the value of the tag must be set to NULL.

0x0009.Name: GpsStatus
0x0009.Description: Specifies the status of the GPS receiver when the image is recorded. 'A' means measurement is in progress, and 'V' means the measurement is Interoperability.

0x000A.Name: GpsMeasureMode
0x000A.Description: Specifies the GPS measurement mode. 2 specifies 2-D measurement, and 3 specifies 3-D measurement.

0x000B.Name: GpsDop
0x000B.Description: GPS DOP (data degree of precision). An HDOP value is written during 2-D measurement, and a PDOP value is written during 3-D measurement.

0x000C.Name: GPSSpeedRef
0x000C.Description: Specifies the unit used to express the GPS receiver speed of movement. K , M , and N represent kilometers per hour, miles per hour, and knots respectively.

0x000D.Name: GPSSpeed
0x000D.Description: Speed of the GPS receiver movement.

0x000E.Name: GPSTrackRef
0x000E.Description: Specifies the reference for giving the direction of GPS receiver movement. T specifies true direction, and M specifies magnetic direction.

0x000F.Name: GPSTrack
0x000F.Description: Direction of GPS receiver movement. The range of values is from 0.00 to 359.99.

0x0010.Name: GPSImgDirRef
0x0010.Description: Specifies the reference for the direction of the image when it is captured. T specifies true direction, and M specifies magnetic direction.

0x0011.Name: GPSImgDir
0x0011.Description: Direction of the image when it was captured. The range of values is from 0.00 to 359.99.

0x0012.Name: GPSMapDatum
0x0012.Description: Indicates the geodetic survey data used by the GPS receiver. If the survey data is restricted to Japan, the value of this tag is 'TOKYO' or 'WGS-84'.

0x0013.Name: GPSDestLatRef
0x0013.Description: Specifies whether the latitude of the destination point is north or south latitude. N specifies north latitude, and S specifies south latitude.

0x0014.Name: GPSDestLat
0x0014.Description: Latitude of the destination point. The latitude is expressed as three rational values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds respectively. When degrees, minutes, and seconds are expressed, the format is dd/1, mm/1, ss/1. When degrees and minutes are used and, for example, fractions of minutes are given up to two decimal places, the format is dd/1, mmmm/100, 0/1.

0x0015.Name: GPSDestLongRef
0x0015.Description: Specifies whether the longitude of the destination point is east or west longitude. E specifies east longitude, and W specifies west longitude.

0x0016.Name: GPSDestLong
0x0016.Description: Longitude of the destination point. The longitude is expressed as three rational values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds respectively. When degrees, minutes, and seconds are expressed, the format is ddd/1, mm/1, ss/1. When degrees and minutes are used and, for example, fractions of minutes are given up to two decimal places, the format is ddd/1, mmmm/100, 0/1.

0x0017.Name: GPSDestBearRef
0x0017.Description: Specifies the reference used for giving the bearing to the destination point. T specifies true direction, and M specifies magnetic direction.

0x0018.Name: GPSDestBear
0x0018.Description: Bearing to the destination point. The range of values is from 0.00 to 359.99.

0x0019.Name: GPSDestDistRef
0x0019.Description: Specifies the unit used to express the distance to the destination point. 'K', 'M', and 'N' represent kilometers, miles, and knots respectively.

0x00FE.Name: NewSubfileType
0x00FE.Description: Type of data in a subfile.

0x00FF.Name: SubfileType
0x00FF.Description: Type of data in a subfile.

0x0102.Name: BitsPerSample
0x0102.Description: Number of bits per color component.

0x0103.Name: Compression
0x0103.Description: Compression scheme used for the image data.

0x0106.Name: PhotometricInterp
0x0106.Description: How pixel data will be interpreted.

0x0107.Name: ThreshHolding
0x0107.Description: Technique used to convert from gray pixels to black and white pixels.

0x0108.Name: CellWidth
0x0108.Description: Width of the dithering or halftoning matrix.

0x0109.Name: CellHeight
0x0109.Description: Height of the dithering or halftoning matrix.

0x010A.Name: FillOrder
0x010A.Description: Logical order of bits in a byte.

0x010D.Name: DocumentName
0x010D.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name of the document from which the image was scanned.

0x010E.Name: ImageDescription
0x010E.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the title of the image.

0x010F.Name: EquipMake
0x010F.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the manufacturer of the equipment used to record the image.

0x0110.Name: EquipModel
0x0110.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the model name or model number of the equipment used to record the image.

0x0111.Name: StripOffsets
0x0111.Description: For each strip, the byte offset of that strip.

0x0112.Name: Orientation
0x0112.Description: Image orientation viewed in terms of rows and columns.

0x0115.Name: SamplesPerPixel
0x0115.Description: Number of color components per pixel.

0x0117.Name: StripBytesCount
0x0117.Description: For each strip, the total number of bytes in that strip.

0x0118.Name: MinSampleValue
0x0118.Description: For each color component, the minimum value assigned to that component.

0x0119.Name: MaxSampleValue
0x0119.Description: For each color component, the maximum value assigned to that component.

0x011A.Name: XResolution
0x011A.Description: Number of pixels per unit in the image width (x) direction. The unit is specified by ResolutionUnit.

0x011B.Name: YResolution
0x011B.Description: Number of pixels per unit in the image height (y) direction. The unit is specified by ResolutionUnit.

0x011C.Name: PlanarConfig
0x011C.Description: Whether pixel components are recorded in chunky or planar format.

0x011D.Name: PageName
0x011D.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name of the page from which the image was scanned.

0x011E.Name: XPosition
0x011E.Description: Offset from the left side of the page to the left side of the image. The unit of measure is specified by ResolutionUnit.

0x011F.Name: YPosition
0x011F.Description: Offset from the top of the page to the top of the image. The unit of measure is specified by ResolutionUnit.

0x0120.Name: FreeOffset
0x0120.Description: For each string of contiguous unused bytes, the byte offset of that string.

0x0121.Name: FreeByteCounts
0x0121.Description: For each string of contiguous unused bytes, the number of bytes in that string.

0x0122.Name: GrayResponseUnit
0x0122.Description: Precision of the number specified by GrayResponseCurve. 1 specifies tenths, 2 specifies hundredths, 3 specifies thousandths, and so on.

0x0123.Name: GrayResponseCurve
0x0123.Description: For each possible pixel value in a grayscale image, the optical density of that pixel value.

0x0124.Name: T4Option
0x0124.Description: Set of flags that relate to T4 encoding.

0x0125.Name: T6Option
0x0125.Description: Set of flags that relate to T6 encoding.

0x0128.Name: ResolutionUnit
0x0128.Description: Unit of measure for the horizontal resolution and the vertical resolution.

0x0129.Name: PageNumber
0x0129.Description: Page number of the page from which the image was scanned.

0x012D.Name: TransferFunction
0x012D.Description: Tables that specify transfer functions for the image.

0x0131.Name: SoftwareUsed
0x0131.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name and version of the software or firmware of the device used to generate the image.

0x0132.Name: DateTime
0x0132.Description: Date and time the image was created.

0x013B.Name: Artist
0x013B.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name of the person who created the image.

0x013C.Name: HostComputer
0x013C.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the computer and/or operating system used to create the image.

0x013D.Name: Predictor
0x013D.Description: Type of prediction scheme that was applied to the image data before the encoding scheme was applied.

0x013E.Name: WhitePoint
0x013E.Description: Chromaticity of the white point of the image.

0x013F.Name: PrimaryChromaticities
0x013F.Description: For each of the three primary colors in the image, the chromaticity of that color.

0x0140.Name: ColorMap
0x0140.Description: Color palette (lookup table) for a palette-indexed image.

0x0141.Name: HalftoneHints
0x0141.Description: Information used by the halftone function

0x0142.Name: TileWidth
0x0142.Description: Number of pixel columns in each tile.

0x0143.Name: TileLength
0x0143.Description: Number of pixel rows in each tile.

0x0144.Name: TileOffset
0x0144.Description: For each tile, the byte offset of that tile.

0x0145.Name: TileByteCounts
0x0145.Description: For each tile, the number of bytes in that tile.

0x014C.Name: InkSet
0x014C.Description: Set of inks used in a separated image.

0x014D.Name: InkNames
0x014D.Description: Sequence of concatenated, null-terminated, character strings that specify the names of the inks used in a separated image.

0x0150.Name: DotRange
0x0150.Description: Color component values that correspond to a 0 percent dot and a 100 percent dot.

0x0151.Name: TargetPrinter
0x0151.Description: Null-terminated character string that describes the intended printing environment.

0x0152.Name: ExtraSamples
0x0152.Description: Number of extra color components. For example, one extra component might hold an alpha value.

0x0153.Name: SampleFormat
0x0153.Description: For each color component, the numerical format (unsigned, signed, floating point) of that component.

0x0154.Name: SMinSampleValue
0x0154.Description: For each color component, the minimum value of that component.

0x0155.Name: SMaxSampleValue
0x0155.Description: For each color component, the maximum value of that component.

0x0156.Name: TransferRange
0x0156.Description: Table of values that extends the range of the transfer function.

0x0201.Name: InterchangeFormat
0x0201.Description: Offset to the start of a JPEG bitstream.

0x0202.Name: InterchangeLength
0x0202.Description: Length, in bytes, of the JPEG bitstream.

0x0205.Name: LosslessPredictors
0x0205.Description: For each color component, a lossless predictor-selection value for that component.

0x0206.Name: PointTransforms
0x0206.Description: For each color component, a point transformation value for that component.

0x0207.Name: QTables
0x0207.Description: For each color component, the offset to the quantization table for that component.

0x0208.Name: DCTables
0x0208.Description: For each color component, the offset to the DC Huffman table (or lossless Huffman table) for that component.

0x0209.Name: ACTables
0x0209.Description: For each color component, the offset to the AC Huffman table for that component.

0x0211.Name: YCbCrCoefficients
0x0211.Description: Coefficients for transformation from RGB to YCbCr image data.

0x0212.Name: YCbCrSubsampling
0x0212.Description: Sampling ratio of chrominance components in relation to the luminance component.

0x0213.Name: YCbCrPositioning
0x0213.Description: Position of chrominance components in relation to the luminance component.

0x0214.Name: REFBlackWhite
0x0214.Description: Reference black point value and reference white point value.

0x0301.Name: Gamma
0x0301.Description: Gamma value attached to the image. The gamma value is stored as a rational number (pair of long) with a numerator of 100000. For example, a gamma value of 2.2 is stored as the pair (100000, 45455).

0x0302.Name: ICCProfileDescriptor
0x0302.Description: Null-terminated character string that identifies an ICC profile.

0x0303.Name: SRGBRenderingIntent
0x0303.Description: How the image should be displayed as defined by the International Color Consortium (ICC).

0x0320.Name: ImageTitle
0x0320.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the title of the image.

0x5001.Name: ResolutionXUnit
0x5001.Description: Units in which to display horizontal resolution.

0x5002.Name: ResolutionYUnit
0x5002.Description: Units in which to display vertical resolution.

0x5003.Name: ResolutionXLengthUnit
0x5003.Description: Units in which to display the image width.

0x5004.Name: ResolutionYLengthUnit
0x5004.Description: Units in which to display the image height.

0x5005.Name: PrintFlags
0x5005.Description: Sequence of one-byte Boolean values that specify printing options.

0x500A.Name: HalftoneLPI
0x500A.Description: Ink's screen frequency, in lines per inch.

0x500F.Name: HalftoneScreen
0x500F.Description: Boolean value that specifies whether to use the printer's default screens.

0x5010.Name: JPEGQuality
0x5010.Description: Private tag used by the Adobe Photoshop format. Not for public use.

0x5011.Name: GridSize
0x5011.Description: Block of information about grids and guides.

0x5013.Name: Width
0x5013.Description: Width, in pixels, of the thumbnail image.

0x5014.Name: Height
0x5014.Description: Height, in pixels, of the thumbnail image.

0x5015.Name: ColorDepth
0x5015.Description: bits per pixel (BPP) for the thumbnail image.

0x5016.Name: Planes
0x5016.Description: Number of color planes for the thumbnail image.

0x5017.Name: RawBytes
0x5017.Description: Byte offset between rows of pixel data.

0x5018.Name: Size
0x5018.Description: Total size, in bytes, of the thumbnail image.

0x5019.Name: CompressedSize
0x5019.Description: Compressed size, in bytes, of the thumbnail image.

0x501A.Name: ColorTransferFunction
0x501A.Description: Table of values that specify color transfer functions.

0x501B.Name: Data
0x501B.Description: Raw thumbnail bits in JPEG or RGB format. Depends on ThumbnailFormat.

0x5020.Name: ImageWidth
0x5020.Description: Number of pixels per row in the thumbnail image.

0x5021.Name: ImageHeight
0x5021.Description: Number of pixel rows in the thumbnail image.

0x5022.Name: BitsPerSample
0x5022.Description: Number of bits per color component in the thumbnail image.

0x5023.Name: Compression
0x5023.Description: Compression scheme used for thumbnail image data.

0x5024.Name: PhotometricInterp
0x5024.Description: How thumbnail pixel data will be interpreted.

0x5025.Name: ImageDescription
0x5025.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the title of the image.

0x5026.Name: EquipMake
0x5026.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the manufacturer of the equipment used to record the thumbnail image.

0x5027.Name: EquipModel
0x5027.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the model name or model number of the equipment used to record the thumbnail image.

0x5028.Name: StripOffsets
0x5028.Description: For each strip in the thumbnail image, the byte offset of that strip.

0x5029.Name: Orientation
0x5029.Description: Thumbnail image orientation in terms of rows and columns.

0x502A.Name: SamplesPerPixel
0x502A.Description: Number of color components per pixel in the thumbnail image.

0x502B.Name: RowsPerStrip
0x502B.Description: Number of rows per strip in the thumbnail image.

0x502C.Name: StripBytesCount
0x502C.Description: For each thumbnail image strip, the total number of bytes in that strip.

0x502D.Name: ResolutionX
0x502D.Description: Thumbnail resolution in the width direction. The resolution unit is given in ThumbnailResolutionUnit.

0x502E.Name: ResolutionY
0x502E.Description: Thumbnail resolution in the height direction. The resolution unit is given in ThumbnailResolutionUnit.

0x502F.Name: PlanarConfig
0x502F.Description: Whether pixel components in the thumbnail image are recorded in chunky or planar format.

0x5030.Name: ResolutionUnit
0x5030.Description: Unit of measure for the horizontal resolution and the vertical resolution of the thumbnail image.

0x5031.Name: TransferFunction
0x5031.Description: Tables that specify transfer functions for the thumbnail image.

0x5032.Name: SoftwareUsed
0x5032.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name and version of the software or firmware of the device used to generate the thumbnail image.

0x5033.Name: DateTime
0x5033.Description: Date and time the thumbnail image was created.

0x5034.Name: Artist
0x5034.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name of the person who created the thumbnail image.

0x5035.Name: WhitePoint
0x5035.Description: Chromaticity of the white point of the thumbnail image.

0x5036.Name: PrimaryChromaticities
0x5036.Description: For each of the three primary colors in the thumbnail image, the chromaticity of that color.

0x5037.Name: YCbCrCoefficients
0x5037.Description: Coefficients for transformation from RGB to YCbCr data for the thumbnail image.

0x5038.Name: YCbCrSubsampling
0x5038.Description: Sampling ratio of chrominance components in relation to the luminance component for the thumbnail image.

0x5039.Name: YCbCrPositioning
0x5039.Description: Position of chrominance components in relation to the luminance component for the thumbnail image.

0x503A.Name: RefBlackWhite
0x503A.Description: Reference black point value and reference white point value for the thumbnail image.

0x503B.Name: CopyRight
0x503B.Description: Null-terminated character string that contains copyright information for the thumbnail image.

0x5090.Name: LuminanceTable
0x5090.Description: Luminance table. The luminance table and the chrominance table are used to control JPEG quality. A valid luminance or chrominance table has 64 entries of type Short. If an image has either a luminance table or a chrominance table, then it must have both tables.

0x5091.Name: ChrominanceTable
0x5091.Description: Chrominance table. The luminance table and the chrominance table are used to control JPEG quality. A valid luminance or chrominance table has 64 entries of type Short. If an image has either a luminance table or a chrominance table, then it must have both tables.

0x5100.Name: FrameDelay
0x5100.Description: Time delay, in hundredths of a second, between two frames in an animated GIF image.

0x5101.Name: LoopCount
0x5101.Description: For an animated GIF image, the number of times to display the animation. A value of 0 specifies that the animation should be displayed infinitely.

0x5111.Name: PixelPerUnitX
0x5111.Description: Pixels per unit in the x direction.

0x5112.Name: PixelPerUnitY
0x5112.Description: Pixels per unit in the y direction.

0x8298.Name: Copyright
0x8298.Description: Null-terminated character string that contains copyright information.

0x8769.Name: IFD
0x8769.Description: Private tag used by GDI+. Not for public use. GDI+ uses this tag to locate Exif-specific information.

0x8773.Name: ICCProfile
0x8773.Description: ICC profile embedded in the image.

0x8822.Name: ExposureProg
0x8822.Description: Class of the program used by the camera to set exposure when the picture is taken.

0x8824.Name: SpectralSense
0x8824.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the spectral sensitivity of each channel of the camera used. The string is compatible with the standard developed by the ASTM Technical Committee.

0x8825.Name: GpsIFD
0x8825.Description: Offset to a block of GPS property items. Property items whose tags have the prefix Gps are stored in the GPS block. The GPS property items are defined in the EXIF specification. GDI+ uses this tag to locate GPS information, but GDI+ does not expose this tag for public use.

0x8827.Name: ISOSpeed
0x8827.Description: ISO speed and ISO latitude of the camera or input device as specified in ISO 12232.

0x8828.Name: OECF
0x8828.Description: Optoelectronic conversion function (OECF) specified in ISO 14524. The OECF is the relationship between the camera optical input and the image values.

0x9000.Name: Ver
0x9000.Description: Version of the EXIF standard supported. Nonexistence of this field is taken to mean nonconformance to the standard. Conformance to the standard is indicated by recording 0210 as a 4-byte ASCII string. Because the type is Undefined, there is no NULL terminator.

0x9003.Name: DTOrig
0x9003.Description: Date and time when the original image data was generated. For a DSC, the date and time when the picture was taken. The format is YYYY:MM:DD HH:MM:SS with time shown in 24-hour format and the date and time separated by one blank character (0x2000). The character string length is 20 bytes including the NULL terminator. When the field is empty, it is treated as unknown.

0x9004.Name: DTDigitized
0x9004.Description: Date and time when the image was stored as digital data. If, for example, an image was captured by DSC and at the same time the file was recorded, then DateTimeOriginal and DateTimeDigitized will have the same contents. The format is YYYY:MM:DD HH:MM:SS with time shown in 24-hour format and the date and time separated by one blank character (0x2000). The character string length is 20 bytes including the NULL terminator. When the field is empty, it is treated as unknown.

0x9101.Name: CompConfig
0x9101.Description: Information specific to compressed data. The channels of each component are arranged in order from the first component to the fourth. For uncompressed data, the data arrangement is given in the PhotometricInterp tag. However, because PhotometricInterp can only express the order of Y, Cb, and Cr, this tag is provided for cases when compressed data uses components other than Y, Cb, and Cr and to support other sequences.

0x9102.Name: CompBPP
0x9102.Description: Information specific to compressed data. The compression mode used for a compressed image is indicated in unit BPP.

0x9201.Name: ShutterSpeed
0x9201.Description: Shutter speed. The unit is the Additive System of Photographic Exposure (APEX) value.

0x9202.Name: Aperture
0x9202.Description: Lens aperture. The unit is the Additive System of Photographic Exposure (APEX) value.

0x9203.Name: Brightness
0x9203.Description: Brightness value. The unit is the Additive System of Photographic Exposure (APEX) value. Ordinarily it is given in the range of -99.99 to 99.99.

0x9204.Name: ExposureBias
0x9204.Description: Exposure bias. The unit is the Additive System of Photographic Exposure (APEX) value. Ordinarily it is given in the range -99.99 to 99.99.

0x9205.Name: MaxAperture
0x9205.Description: Smallest F number of the lens. The unit is the Additive System of Photographic Exposure (APEX) value. Ordinarily it is given in the range of 00.00 to 99.99, but it is not limited to this range.

0x9206.Name: SubjectDist
0x9206.Description: Distance to the subject, measured in meters.

0x9209.Name: Flash
0x9209.Description: Flash status. This tag is recorded when an image is taken using a strobe light (flash). Bit 0 indicates the flash firing status, and bits 1 and 2 indicate the flash return status.

0x920A.Name: FocalLength
0x920A.Description: Actual focal length, in millimeters, of the lens. Conversion is not made to the focal length of a 35 millimeter film camera.

0x9213.Name: ImageHistory
0x9213.Description: Record of what has been done to the image.

0x927C.Name: MakerNote
0x927C.Description: Note tag. A tag used by manufacturers of EXIF writers to record information. The contents are up to the manufacturer.

0x9286.Name: UserComment
0x9286.Description: Comment tag. A tag used by EXIF users to write keywords or comments about the image besides those in ImageDescription and without the character-code limitations of the ImageDescription tag.

0x9290.Name: DTSubsec
0x9290.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies a fraction of a second for the DateTime tag.

0x9291.Name: DTOrigSS
0x9291.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies a fraction of a second for the ExifDTOrig tag.

0x9292.Name: DTDigSS
0x9292.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies a fraction of a second for the ExifDTDigitized tag.

0x9C9B.Name: XPTitle
0x9C9B.Description: Title tag used by Windows, encoded in UCS2

0x9C9C.Name: XPComment
0x9C9C.Description: Comment tag used by Windows, encoded in UCS2

0x9C9D.Name: XPAuthor
0x9C9D.Description: Author tag used by Windows, encoded in UCS2

0x9C9E.Name: XPKeywords
0x9C9E.Description: Keywords tag used by Windows, encoded in UCS2

0x9C9F.Name: XPSubject
0x9C9F.Description: Subject tag used by Windows, encoded in UCS2

0xA000.Name: FPXVer
0xA000.Description: FlashPix format version supported by an FPXR file. If the FPXR function supports FlashPix format version 1.0, this is indicated similarly to ExifVer by recording 0100 as a 4-byte ASCII string. Because the type is Undefined, there is no NULL terminator.

0xA001.Name: ColorSpace
0xA001.Description: Color space specifier. Normally sRGB (=1) is used to define the color space based on the PC monitor conditions and environment. If a color space other than sRGB is used, Uncalibrated (=0xFFFF) is set. Image data recorded as Uncalibrated can be treated as sRGB when it is converted to FlashPix.

0xA002.Name: PixXDim
0xA002.Description: Information specific to compressed data. When a compressed file is recorded, the valid width of the meaningful image must be recorded in this tag, whether or not there is padding data or a restart marker. This tag should not exist in an uncompressed file.

0xA003.Name: PixYDim
0xA003.Description: Information specific to compressed data. When a compressed file is recorded, the valid height of the meaningful image must be recorded in this tag whether or not there is padding data or a restart marker. This tag should not exist in an uncompressed file. Because data padding is unnecessary in the vertical direction, the number of lines recorded in this valid image height tag will be the same as that recorded in the SOF.

0xA004.Name: RelatedWav
0xA004.Description: The name of an audio file related to the image data. The only relational information recorded is the EXIF audio file name and extension (an ASCII string that consists of 8 characters plus a period (.), plus 3 characters). The path is not recorded. When you use this tag, audio files must be recorded in conformance with the EXIF audio format. Writers can also store audio data within APP2 as FlashPix extension stream data.

0xA005.Name: Interop
0xA005.Description: Offset to a block of property items that contain interoperability information.

0xA20B.Name: FlashEnergy
0xA20B.Description: Strobe energy, in Beam Candle Power Seconds (BCPS), at the time the image was captured.

0xA20C.Name: SpatialFR
0xA20C.Description: Camera or input device spatial frequency table and SFR values in the image width, image height, and diagonal direction, as specified in ISO 12233.

0xA20E.Name: FocalXRes
0xA20E.Description: Number of pixels in the image width (x) direction per unit on the camera focal plane. The unit is specified in ExifFocalResUnit.

0xA20F.Name: FocalYRes
0xA20F.Description: Number of pixels in the image height (y) direction per unit on the camera focal plane. The unit is specified in ExifFocalResUnit.

0xA210.Name: FocalResUnit
0xA210.Description: Unit of measure for ExifFocalXRes and ExifFocalYRes.

0xA214.Name: SubjectLoc
0xA214.Description: Location of the main subject in the scene. The value of this tag represents the pixel at the center of the main subject relative to the left edge. The first value indicates the column number, and the second value indicates the row number.

0xA215.Name: ExposureIndex
0xA215.Description: Exposure index selected on the camera or input device at the time the image was captured.

0xA217.Name: SensingMethod
0xA217.Description: Image sensor type on the camera or input device.

0xA300.Name: FileSource
0xA300.Description: The image source. If a DSC recorded the image, the value of this tag is 3.

0xA301.Name: SceneType
0xA301.Description: The type of scene. If a DSC recorded the image, the value of this tag must be set to 1, indicating that the image was directly photographed.

0xA302.Name: CfaPattern
0xA302.Description: The color filter array (CFA) geometric pattern of the image sensor when a one-chip color area sensor is used. It does not apply to all sensing methods.
